    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-04-02</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2026-05-05T21:43:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Aviation Medication Transparency Act of 2025</strong></p><p>This bill directs the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to compile, publish, and annually update a list of medications that may be safely prescribed to pilots and air traffic controllers for the purposes of issuing a medical certification. The list must be publicly available on the FAA website and distributed to those seeking a license and medical&nbsp;certification. </p><p>Currently, the FAA does not have a list of approved medications. However, the FAA does have lists for Aviation Medical Examiners of <em>Do Not Issue</em> medications and <em>Do Not Fly</em> medications.<em></em></p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Aviation Medication Transparency Act of 2025</title>
